title: World2_Intro
position: -701,-715
---
// This node fires automatically when the player first enters the world.
<<set_left mc_surprised>>
<<enter_left>>
<<highlight left>>

MC: No way this actually worked.. But why does everything feel so flat?!

<<set_right Akane>>
<<enter_right>>
<<highlight right>>

Child: You said it so yourself — these are after all... pretty old terminals. They can only handle so much.

<<highlight left>>
MC: Uhh.. I see.

<<highlight right>>
Child: You are a new resident of this utopia. You were invited here by your friend. Explore this place.
Speak to those you meet. And then I'll decide what kind of person you are.

<<exit_right>>
<<exit_left>>
===

title: World2_Stranger
position: 497,-501
---
<<set_left mc_neutral>>
<<set_right stranger_smiling>>
<<enter_left>>
<<enter_right>>
<<highlight right>>

Stranger: Ah, a new face. Welcome to the only utopia in this world!

<<highlight left>>
-> Um, can you tell me a bit more about this place?
    <<jump World2_Stranger_Explain>>
-> This place is a utopia?
    <<jump World2_Stranger_Explain>>
===

title: World2_Stranger_Explain
position: 600,-178
---
<<highlight right>>
Stranger: Yes indeed. It is known that a utopia is not possible because of several factors — then how is it that this land knows no suffering, no conflict, only bliss?
Stranger: The answer lies at the boundary of this land. There is a child kept in darkness, constantly suffering.
His suffering sustains this utopia. As long as that child suffers, this place endures.

<<set_left mc_surprised>>
<<highlight left>>
-> Wh— what..? And you are fine with it?
    <<set $stranger_response = 1>>
    <<jump World2_Stranger_Response>>
-> Do people know this?
    <<set $stranger_response = 2>>
    <<jump World2_Stranger_Response>>
===

title: World2_Stranger_Response
position: 840,79
---
<<if $stranger_response == 1>>
    <<highlight right>>
    Stranger: Yes I am. If it means my friends and family live their perfect life, I can sit comfortably sacrificing a single life.
    
    <<set_left mc_neutral>>
    <<highlight left>>
    MC: That is... understandable.

<<else>>
    <<highlight right>>
    Stranger: Every resident is aware of this fact. None of them object. After all, who would give up a perfect life?
    
    <<set_left mc_angry>>
    <<highlight left>>
    MC: This is insane. That child is innocent.

    <<highlight right>>
    Stranger: He is. Although it does not matter. Humans are naturally inclined toward self-interest. Spend more time here and you will understand.
<<endif>>

<<set_left mc_neutral>>
<<highlight right>>
Stranger: All it takes to break this utopia is to free the child. Think carefully before you act. People's lives are at stake.

// The C# Manager now knows you finished talking to the Stranger!
<<complete_objective stranger>>

<<exit_right>>
<<exit_left>>
===

